 :tx/rationale "UAQ INSIGHT 1: FIVE INDEPENDENT OPTIMIZATION SYSTEMS. Braid currently has five independent systems that each decide what to recommend/show/measure, each with separate weights and calibration: (1) R(t) routing — 6-feature weighted score for task ranking, hardcoded DEFAULT_ROUTING_WEIGHTS. (2) ACP attention — static OutputPrecedence ordering for context blocks, no learning. (3) F(S) boundaries — bootstrap policy boundary weights, only HL-CALIBRATE wiring exists (not yet producing real adjustments). (4) Ceremony level — k_eff threshold mapping to Full/Standard/Minimal, no learning. (5) Harvest urgency — 4-signal max() function, no learning. These systems don't share information. R(t) doesn't know which context blocks were useful. ACP doesn't know which tasks got completed. F(S) boundaries don't know which ceremony level produced best outcomes. Each optimizes its narrow objective without seeing the whole picture. This is the open loop that subsumes all other open loops. SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-019 (Universal Action Queue), ADR-FOUNDATION-024 (Learned Attention). VERIFICATION: After unification, all five decision types should be scored by one function, and calibration data from any type should improve predictions for all types."
